#Text=Underclock a PC

#Text=PCs are under-clocked for considerably longer hardware lifespan , reduced heat generation ( and hence dissipation ) , reduced electrical power consumption , increased stability and reduced noise from mechanical cooling parts .
#Text=Steps
#Text=Access the computer 's BIOS settings page ( BIOS stands for " Basic Input Output System " ) .

column1: #Text=Depending on brand of computer , this requires pressing keys during a certain time of the boot process .
#Text=Some manufacturers require pressing " Delete " " F2 " or " alt"+ or other key combination while the system goes through POST ( Power On Self Test ) or displays a logo on the screen .
#Text=Image : Underclock a PC
#Text=Step 1 . jpg
#Text=Locate " Frequency/Voltage Control " settings .

column1: #Text=BIOS screens generally consist of several pages of settings .
#Text=Each page relates directly to certain parts of the computer operation .
#Text=Use the " PgDn " and " PgUp " or " " arrow keys to navigate to the page that allows for adjustment of the above variables .
#Text=Image : Underclock a PC Step 2 Version 2 . jpg
#Text=Scroll down to the " CPU Frequency/Voltage Control . "

column1: #Text=Press " Enter " or use the left and right arrow keys to select the value .
#Text=Use the arrow keys , + and - keys or other combination to adjust the value lower .
#Text=Image : Underclock a PC Step 3 Version 2 . jpg
#Text=Lower the CPU clock speed .
#Text=Lower these values similar to the way described above .
#Text=Note that the performance decreases linearly to the clock speed .
#Text=Image : Underclock a PC Step 5 Version 2 . jpg
#Text=Lower the core voltage ( vCore ) .
#Text=Lower these values similar to the way described above .
#Text=In the CPU 's spec it will mostly behave linearly , so a 10 % decrease in voltage will need about a 10 % decrease in clock speed .
#Text=Image : Underclock a PC Step 6 Version 2 . jpg
#Text=When complete , be sure to save the settings before exiting , otherwise the old settings will remain in place .
#Text=If you think you 've made a mistake , press the " Esc " key to exit without saving .
#Text=Note : Not all computer BIOS have " Frequency/Voltage Control " settings , maybe lock by Manufacturers .

column1: #Text=Image : Underclock a PC
#Text=Step 7 Version 2 .
#Text=jpg
#Text=" alt "
#Text=Tips
#Text=Locate or download and print a copy of the system board or computer manual 's BIOS section .
#Text=The exact BIOS access method will be described here , along with additional information on this subject and the other values in the BIOS pages .
#Text=If you are unable to boot because of wrong values , reset the BIOS to " default "

#Text=This can be accomplished by removing BIOS battery for ten minutes or so before replacing , or inserting or removing a jumper on pins on the system board , or other method described in the manual and powering on the system .
#Text=Warnings
#Text=Underclocking reduces overall performance .
#Text=Underclocking voids the system warranty on most computers , depending on the manufacturer .
#Text=Do not enter a Password for the BIOS screen that you can not remember .
#Text=A full BIOS reset may be required to clear the password .
#Text=The manual may explain methods to clear forgotten passwords if this happens .
